23/09/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatia will host a weekend conference on the future of Southeast Europe and EU integration prospects, organisers said Wednesday (22 September).
Participants will discuss issues such as restoring understanding and trust in the region, the challenges and opportunities of EU integration, and regional cultural identity.
The conference starts Saturday and is to be attended by the presidents of Croatia, Serbia-Montenegro, and Bosnia and Herzegovina, as well as by OSCE officials.
(HINA, HRT - 22/09/04)
